{"overview":"This 57-bar piece in E minor is cast in a rounded ternary form (A–B–A''–Coda) with a brooding, lyrical character shaped by pervasive arpeggiated accompaniment and a sighing melodic contour; its most distinctive harmonic feature is a smooth diatonic chain of thirds through B major and C# minor in the middle section, framed by dense chromatic intensification via diminished-seventh chords and secondary dominants in the outer sections.","cross_piece_tags":["nocturne","ternary","arpeggiated_bass","lyrical","melancholic","meditative","circle_of_fifths","modal_mixture"]}
